finding the places it describes on a map, or arriving at a conclusion about the social reality experienced by a historical community of redactors. These utopian goals are projected onto a utopian text. This volume advocates an honest hermeneutical approach to the question of how reliably a past reality can be reconstructed from a biblical passage, and it aims to provide an example of disclosing – not obscuring – pre-suppositions brought to the text.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aReligion and geography. 4aAltes Testament. 4aBibelrezeption. 4aHermeneutik. 4aUtopie. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aHebrew Bible.  ahermeneutics.  ascience fiction.  autopia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies De Gruyterz97831107168250 cEPUBz97831104142710 cprintz978311041154640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041417240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110414172423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110414172/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-071682-5  Religious Studies De Gruyter  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_E